        <h1>Med Spa Marketing Cost in Miami (2026 Pricing Guide)</h1>
        <p class="lead">What does med spa marketing actually cost? Pricing breakdown by service. Compare national agencies, local specialists, and when to DIY.</p>
        <div class="post-meta">
          <span>May 18, 2026</span>
          <span>9 min read</span>
          <span>Agency Pricing</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <img
        class="hero-cover"
        src="/blog/hero-med-spa-marketing-cost-miami.webp"
        alt="Modern Miami medical spa treatment room interior with a crisp white-linen treatment bed, stainless-and-brass rolling cart of clinical accessories at the bedside, and warm afternoon sunlight raking through linen curtains"
        title="Med Spa Marketing Cost in Miami"
        width="1600"
        height="900"
        loading="eager"
        fetchpriority="high"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="blog-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="blog-body">

        <p>Most Miami med spas pay between $500 and $5,000 per month to a marketing agency. But the actual cost depends on what you're buying: basic SEO and review management versus full-service Google Ads, social media, and content. Some clinics spend $297 monthly on Google Business Profile optimization. Others spend $8,000 just on Google Ads, plus agency fees on top. The wide range isn't confusing once you understand what each service actually costs and delivers.</p>

        <p>Your next decision isn't "how much should I spend" but "what's worth spending on?" A Botox treatment generates $500 to $900 per patient. High-value med spa patients generate significant lifetime revenue. A patient returning 4-6 times annually for treatments spanning years accumulates $2,000-$5,000 or more in total value. If marketing brings in one new high-value patient every two months, you've already paid for a year of service. This guide shows you exactly what you're paying for, what agencies charge nationally and locally, and how to know if the price is fair.</p>

        <div class="key-takeaways">
          <strong>Key Takeaways</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>SEO costs $497-$2,500/mo; Google Ads require $1,500-$8,000/mo including ad spend</li>
            <li>High-value med spa customers generate $2,000-$5,000+ lifetime value over multiple visits</li>
            <li>Local Miami agencies charge 30-40% less than national firms for same services</li>
            <li>Month-to-month contracts only; any agency demanding annual lock-in is a red flag</li>
            <li>ROI timeline: paid ads 1-2 weeks, SEO 60-90 days, reputation management immediate</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>What Med Spa Marketing Actually Includes</h2>

        <p>When you hire a med spa marketing agency, you're not paying one price for "marketing." You're paying for specific services that work together. Understanding what each one does prevents overpaying for services you don't need or underinvesting in channels that drive real results for med spas.</p>

        <p>SEO (search engine optimization) is the most valuable channel for medical aesthetics clinics. When someone searches "Botox Miami" or "med spa near Coral Gables," your clinic either appears in the top three or doesn't get the call (here is <a href="/blog/how-miami-med-spas-rank-botox-near-me/">exactly how Miami med spas rank for "botox near me"</a>). SEO takes months to build but costs nothing per click once it's working. And whatever you spend on traffic, <a href="/blog/botox-filler-marketing-what-books-consults/">what actually books the consult</a> is the system that catches the lead.</p>

        <p>Google Business Profile management is the fastest win. It's the business card Google shows when someone searches your location or service. Includes claiming your profile, adding photos, managing reviews, and weekly posts. Most small agencies charge $297 to $497 per month.</p>

        <p>Google Ads (paid search) puts your clinic at the top for high-intent searches immediately. Budget starts at $1,500 per month total (including the ad spend itself). You pay for clicks, not results, so it requires active management to stay profitable.</p>

        <p>Social media ads run on Facebook, Instagram, and TikTok. Med spas get strong ROI on before-and-after content aimed at local audiences. Budget typically starts at $500 per month for ad spend, plus agency fees.</p>

        <p>Website design and development is the foundation. A weak website kills conversions even if marketing brings traffic. Ranges from $2,500 for a basic template to $15,000 for fully custom design with booking integration.</p>

        <p>Reputation management (review generation and response) has the highest ROI. Practices that actively generate reviews and respond to them see 35% more revenue than those that ignore reviews (per Womply, 2019).</p>

