        <h2>Med Spa Marketing Cost Breakdown by Service</h2>

        <p>Here's what each service costs when you buy it individually or as part of a package. These are real prices from established agencies operating in Miami and nationally.</p>

        <h3>SEO (Search Engine Optimization)</h3>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Basic local SEO:</strong> $497-$800/month (includes on-page optimization, content, local citations, review support)</li>
          <li><strong>Intermediate SEO:</strong> $1,200-$2,000/month (adds technical SEO, link building, content strategy)</li>
          <li><strong>Enterprise SEO:</strong> $2,500+/month (includes competitor analysis, custom research, dedicated account team)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>WebFX, a national agency, charges $2,500-$10,000 per month for SEO depending on package. Local Miami agencies typically charge 40% less for the same service because they have lower overhead. In our experience running <a href="/medspas/seo/">med spa SEO</a> at Thryv, med spas with $800-$1,200 monthly SEO investment start seeing consistent organic traffic in 90-120 days.</p>

        <h3>Google Business Profile Management</h3>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Self-managed:</strong> $0 (but takes your time each week)</li>
          <li><strong>Agency management:</strong> $297-$497/month (includes photo management, review requests, weekly posts, response monitoring)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>This is the service with the best ROI-per-dollar. Profiles with 100+ photos receive 520% more calls than sparse profiles (per BrightLocal). If you're choosing between GBP management and SEO, choose GBP first.</p>

        <h3>Google Ads (Paid Search)</h3>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Ad spend budget:</strong> $1,500-$8,000/month (this is what you pay Google for clicks)</li>
          <li><strong>Agency management fee:</strong> 15-25% of ad spend, or flat $500-$1,500/month</li>
          <li><strong>Total monthly cost:</strong> $1,725-$10,000 depending on spend level and agency</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Most med spas shouldn't start Google Ads below $1,500/month total. Below that, you don't accumulate enough data to optimize effectively. Average cost-per-click for med spa keywords is $2-$5 in Miami depending on competitiveness.</p>

        <h3>Social Media Ads (Facebook, Instagram, TikTok)</h3>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Ad spend:</strong> $500-$3,000/month (this is what you pay the platform for impressions and clicks)</li>
          <li><strong>Agency management fee:</strong> $300-$800/month or 15-20% of spend</li>
          <li><strong>Total:</strong> $300-$3,800/month depending on volume</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Facebook and Instagram are highly effective for med spa before-and-after content targeting women 25-55 in Miami neighborhoods. TikTok has lower costs but smaller audience overlap with your demographic.</p>

        <h3>Website Design</h3>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Template-based design:</strong> $2,500-$5,000 (Wix, Squarespace, WordPress theme with minimal customization)</li>
          <li><strong>Custom design:</strong> $7,500-$15,000 (built from scratch, includes booking integration, custom features)</li>
          <li><strong>Enterprise custom design:</strong> $15,000+ (full-stack, advanced animations, complex workflows)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Med spa websites need clear before-and-after galleries, service menu with pricing, booking integration, and testimonials. Cheap templates miss conversion opportunities. Mid-range custom design ($7,500-$10,000) is the sweet spot for most new clinics.</p>

        <h3>Reputation Management (Review Generation)</h3>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Basic review support:</strong> $297-$497/month (email templates, review request automation, response monitoring)</li>
          <li><strong>Full reputation management:</strong> $800-$1,500/month (includes review generation campaigns, negative review response, review amplification)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Practices that send review requests to 100% of patients monthly dramatically increase their review volume. The cost per review generated is typically $15-$40 depending on response rate.</p>

        <h2>Three Pricing Tiers in the Med Spa Marketing Market</h2>

        <p>The market breaks into three clear tiers. Where you fall depends on your clinic stage and budget.</p>

        <h3>Tier 1: DIY + Budget Services ($0-$800/month)</h3>

        <p>You handle most marketing yourself. You pay for Google Business Profile optimization, basic SEO, or a content calendar tool. This tier works only if you have 5-10 hours per week to manage marketing. You'll generate leads, but you'll grow slower than agencies can deliver.</p>

        <p>Realistic expectation: 1-2 new patients per month from organic search after 120 days. No paid ads means no high-intent traffic.</p>

        <h3>Tier 2: Hybrid Agency ($800-$2,500/month)</h3>

        <p>You hire a local Miami agency for SEO, GBP management, and review generation. You manage your own social media or pay a freelancer $300-$500 monthly. You run small Google or Facebook Ads campaigns or skip them. This is the most common tier for established med spas with 3-5 years in business and $500K-$2M annual revenue.</p>

        <p>Realistic expectation: 3-5 new patients per month from organic and paid search combined, within 90-120 days.</p>

        <h3>Tier 3: Full-Service Agency ($2,500+/month)</h3>

        <p>National agencies like WebFX, PatientGain, or Influx Marketing handle everything. SEO, Google Ads ($2,000-$5,000/month spend), social media, website maintenance, reputation management. You get a dedicated account manager and quarterly strategy meetings. Best for high-revenue clinics or new clinics with significant investment capital.</p>

        <p>PatientGain, which specializes in med spa marketing, charges $999-$1,999 per month for their core package, per their public pricing page. Influx Marketing charges $2,000-$5,000 monthly for combined SEO and Google Ads management.</p>

        <p>Realistic expectation: 5-10+ new patients per month depending on local competition and service mix.</p>

