        <h2>What You Should Actually Pay Based on Your Clinic Stage</h2>

        <p>Budget recommendations depend on where your clinic is in its lifecycle. Overspending early wastes money. Underspending later costs you market share.</p>

        <h3>New Med Spa (First 6 Months)</h3>

        <p>Budget $3,500-$6,000 for month one (including website). Then $1,500-$2,000 monthly ongoing.</p>

        <p>Priorities: website, Google Business Profile optimization, Google Ads to drive immediate traffic, basic SEO. Don't hire a full-service agency yet. You need quick wins while SEO builds. New clinics should expect 1-3 new patients monthly in months 1-3, ramping to 5+ by month 4-6.</p>

        <h3>Growing Med Spa (6-24 Months Old, $300K-$800K Revenue)</h3>

        <p>Budget $2,000-$3,500 monthly. Shift from Tier 1 (DIY) or Tier 2 (hybrid) into solid Tier 2 with professional management across all channels.</p>

        <p>Increase SEO spend to $1,200 if you're below that. Run consistent Google Ads at $1,500+ monthly. Add reputation management if you haven't. Most growing clinics see 4-8 new patients monthly with this investment.</p>

        <h3>Established Med Spa ($800K+ Annual Revenue, 2+ Years)</h3>

        <p>Budget $2,500-$5,000+ monthly depending on competitive market and growth goals. You can absorb the cost of full-service agencies. If you're in hot markets like Brickell, <a href="/medspas/seo/miami/miami-beach/">Miami Beach</a>, or Coral Gables with heavy competitor spend, budget higher.</p>

        <p>At this stage, the question isn't "can we afford $3,000 monthly marketing?" but "can we afford NOT to?" One new high-value patient pays for a month of full-service marketing. Established clinics in Tier 3 should expect 8-15+ new patients monthly.</p>

        <h2>Red Flags in Med Spa Marketing Pricing</h2>

        <p>Some agencies use pricing tactics that make it harder to evaluate whether you're getting fair value. Watch for these patterns.</p>

        <h3>Long-Term Contracts</h3>

        <p>Any agency demanding 12-month or longer commitment is signaling they lack confidence results will speak for themselves. Marketing should work fast enough to prove value. If an agency requires a contract, walk. You want month-to-month so you can scale up, down, or switch if results aren't there.</p>

        <h3>No Transparency on Ad Spend</h3>

        <p>If they won't show you what they're spending on Google Ads or Facebook Ads monthly, they're hiding something. You should see itemized bills: $1,500 to Google, $300 agency fee. Anything less is a red flag.</p>

        <h3>Guaranteed Results</h3>

        <p>"We guarantee you'll rank #1 for Botox Miami" is a lie. Google doesn't allow guarantees. Any agency making promises they can't control is overconfident and likely inexperienced.</p>

        <h3>Flat Rates Far Below Market</h3>

        <p>If you find an agency charging $299/month for full SEO management, they're cutting corners. Either they have hundreds of low-attention clients or they'll pivot you to expensive services you don't need once you sign. Quality SEO costs $500+.</p>

        <h3>No Performance Reporting</h3>

        <p>You should get monthly reports showing: organic traffic, conversions, ad spend breakdown, leads generated, cost per lead. If they're vague on results, they're not invested in your success.</p>

        <h2>ROI Math: When Does Med Spa Marketing Pay Back?</h2>

        <div class="inline-tool-cta">
          <strong>Skip the napkin math.</strong>
          <p>Plug your treatment price, monthly marketing budget, and lifetime value into our free calculator and see live ROI estimates for new patients, year-one revenue, and 5-year value.</p>
          <a href="/free-tools/med-spa-marketing-roi-calculator/" class="btn-blue">
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
            Open the ROI Calculator
          </a>
        </div>

        <p>Let's do the real math so you know what to expect. Start with conservative assumptions.</p>

        <h3>The Numbers</h3>

        <p>Average Botox treatment cost: $500-$900. High-value med spa customers accumulate $2,000-$5,000 or more in lifetime value through repeat treatments. Cost per qualified lead from Google Ads: $5-$15. Cost per qualified lead from organic SEO: $0 (no direct cost).</p>

        <p>In our experience working with Miami med spas, 20-30% of qualified leads convert to a booking. Of those bookings, 40-50% show up. Of those who show up, 70-80% complete at least one treatment. So one qualified lead has roughly a 6-12% chance of becoming a paying customer.</p>

        <h3>Google Ads Example</h3>

        <p>Monthly budget: $1,500 (includes $1,000 ad spend, $500 agency fee). At $5-$15 cost per click, you get 67-200 clicks per month. At 6-12% conversion to customer, you get 4-24 new customers monthly. At $600 average first treatment, that's $2,400-$14,400 in revenue from $1,500 spent. Payback: immediate to negative ROI if you get fewer conversions.</p>

        <p>This is why Google Ads is high-risk high-reward. Results depend entirely on your website quality, booking process, and treatment quality.</p>

        <h3>SEO Example</h3>

        <p>Monthly cost: $800. Timeline: 90-120 days to see meaningful organic traffic. Once it's working (month 4+), you're generating 50-200 organic visits per month. At the same 6-12% conversion rate, that's 3-24 new customers monthly, zero additional cost. Payback: 3-4 months of investment, then pure profit.</p>

        <p>SEO is lower risk, longer wait, but superior lifetime ROI.</p>

        <h3>Google Business Profile + Review Generation</h3>

        <p>Monthly cost: $400 (GBP management + review requests). Practices generating 20-30 reviews monthly see significantly more calls than those generating 5 reviews monthly. If 10% of calls convert to bookings, strong review management brings 6-12 new patients per month at $400 monthly investment. ROI: massive. Payback: month 1.</p>

        <h2>National Agencies vs Local Miami Specialists: What's Fair</h2>

        <p>National agencies like WebFX, PatientGain, and Influx Marketing have resources and case studies. Local Miami agencies have neighborhood knowledge and flexibility. Here's how they compare on cost and service quality.</p>

        <h3>National Agencies</h3>

        <p>WebFX (national, multi-service): $2,500-$10,000/month. PatientGain (med spa specialist): $999-$1,999/month. Influx Marketing (med spa + beauty specialist): $2,000-$5,000/month for combined packages.</p>

        <p>Pros: established process, case study portfolio, enterprise-level reporting, team of specialists. Cons: less local market knowledge, higher cost, less flexible on package customization, longer sales cycle.</p>

        <h3>Local Miami Agencies</h3>

        <p>Typical range: $800-$2,500/month depending on services. Many local agencies work as solo operators or small teams of 2-3 people.</p>

        <p>Pros: know Miami neighborhoods (Brickell, Miami Beach, Wynwood, Coral Gables, Doral), flexible on pricing and package, faster decision-making, easier to reach account manager. Cons: smaller team means less specialization, fewer case studies, potentially less process maturity.</p>

        <p>Fair pricing rule: local agencies should cost 30-40% less than national firms for equivalent services. If a local Miami agency is charging the same as WebFX, you're paying national-level prices for local-level resources.</p>

        <p>For a side-by-side rundown of named agencies, see our <a href="/blog/best-med-spa-seo-agencies-miami-2026/">comparison of the top 12 med spa SEO agencies serving Miami</a>.</p>

        <h2>FAQ: Med Spa Marketing Cost</h2>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How much does med spa marketing cost in Miami?</summary>
          <p>Most Miami med spas pay between $500 and $5,000 per month. Basic GBP management starts at $297-$497. Full-service agencies charge $1,500-$3,000 monthly for SEO, ads, and content. National agencies range $999-$10,000. Your total cost depends on which services you buy and your clinic stage.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What does a med spa marketing budget look like for a new clinic?</summary>
          <p>Month one: $3,500-$6,000 (includes website design or setup, GBP optimization, initial ads). Months 2+: $1,500-$2,000 monthly for SEO, GBP management, and Google Ads. Establish the foundation first. New clinics shouldn't try full-service at $5,000/month until they're generating revenue to support it.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is med spa SEO worth the cost?</summary>
          <p>Absolutely. One high-value med spa customer generates $2,000-$5,000 lifetime value through repeat visits. If SEO costs $800/month and brings one new customer every two months, you've paid for a year of service with a single customer. SEO is the best long-term investment because it costs nothing per click once ranking.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How long until I see ROI from med spa marketing?</summary>
          <p>Google Ads: 1-2 weeks. Organic SEO: 60-120 days. Review management: immediately (first week). Most clinics see positive ROI within 3-4 months if they maintain consistent spend and manage the process correctly. Don't expect results in week two from SEO.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What's the cheapest way to market a med spa?</summary>
          <p>Google Business Profile management ($297-$497/month) has the highest ROI-per-dollar. It's free to optimize and generates organic calls with no ad spend. Combine with asking every patient for reviews and posting free content on social media. Add paid ads only after you've maximized organic channels.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Should I hire a national or local Miami med spa marketing agency?</summary>
          <p>Local if you want neighborhood targeting and lower cost. National if you need enterprise resources and have higher budget. For most Miami med spas, local agencies deliver better ROI because they understand your specific market (Brickell, Miami Beach, Coral Gables, Wynwood, Doral) and cost 30-40% less.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do most Miami med spas pay monthly or annually?</summary>
          <p>Month-to-month is the market standard. No reputable agency locks you into annual contracts. If an agency requires 12 months, it's a red flag that they lack confidence in results. You should be able to switch or cancel if ROI isn't there after 90-120 days.</p>
        </details>

        <div class="blog-cta">
          <h2>Get Clear Pricing for Your Clinic</h2>
          <p>Not all med spa marketing agencies are priced fairly. We offer transparent, month-to-month contracts for SEO, Google Ads, and GBP management starting at <a href="/pricing/">Thryv's published rates</a>. No hidden fees. No long-term lock-in. Let's talk about what your clinic actually needs.</p>
